-- Texas Rangers Win Negotiating Rights to Japanese Pitcher Darvish, MLB Says
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2011-12-20T04:18:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-20/texas-rangers-win-negotiating-rights-to-japanese-pitcher-darvish-mlb-says.html
The  Texas Rangers  have won the
bidding rights to Japanese pitcher Yu Darvish and will have 30
days to try to reach a deal,  Major League Baseball  said tonight.  The Hokkaido Nippon Ham Fighters said in an e-mail that
they had accepted a bid to negotiate with Darvish.  Neither MLB not the Fighters gave details on the amount of
the bid.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  